  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "As shown above, the entity types differ greatly in all datasets in Spanish or English.",
    "Since the objective of this study is to build a single efficient bilingual NER system, the use of a dataset of each language for a single model is not viable, as might be the case for the general domain using the CONLL task's dataset for Spanish and English.",
    "Rather, this would bring inconsistency and poor performance to the NER system.",
    "Early Named Entity Recognition systems utilised rule-based methods in which techniques such as transducers (Appelt et al., 1995), pattern matching on dictionaries (Grishman, 1995), and lexical pattern matching (Weischedel, 1995) were used obtaining as high as 94 F-1 scores.",
    "Although these systems performed well, considerable human effort was required for writing the rules and maintaining them."
  ],
